summaries.short: Andy Cohen makes a surprise appearance to fill in for a missing guest, and Josh Groban takes Oscar’s lead in singing a “trashy” refrain.
summaries.full: It’s time for Elmo’s show, but his first guest, Grover is nowhere to be found! Not to worry, Andy Cohen steps in to do his best impression of the MIA monster, while Josh Groban takes Oscar’s lead in singing a “trashy” refrain.

summaries.short: The countdown for jammie time is on as Elmo welcomes Olivia Wilde, Sara Bareilles, and some special friends.
summaries.full: The Count helps Elmo keep an eye on the clock in preparation for jammie time. Elmo welcomes Olivia Wilde for a game of “Teddy Bear Dress Up.” Musical guest Sara Bareilles brings out two of her besties -- plus an extra special Sesame Street friend -- to help her perform her very own version of “Twinkle Twinkle Little Star.”

titles.short: Mykal-Michelle Harris / Jonathan Van Ness / H.E.R
titles.full: Mykal-Michelle Harris / Jonathan Van Ness / H.E.R

summaries.short: Mykal-Michelle Harris co-hosts, Jonathan Van Ness unleashes his monster makeover talents, and H.E.R. sings a song about her cherished hair.
summaries.full: Elmo brings in "monster makeover specialist" Jonathan Van Ness to unleash the gorgeous monster inside Sesame Streeter Alan, before Elmo and Cookie unveil hair and makeup transformations of their own. Mykal-Michelle Harris gives hosting a whirl and faces off with Elmo in a "No Laugh Challenge," and H.E.R. performs a song about her beautiful, versatile hair.

summaries.short: Elmo and Jason Sudeikis embrace potty time, and Ciara sings an inspiring song.
summaries.full: Elmo isn’t shy about an important part of his bedtime routine: potty time! After he challenges Jason Sudeikis to a round of the "Silly Dance Game," Ciara stops by to share an inspiring musical message. Meanwhile, Grover shakes things up as he plays usher.

summaries.short: Elmo learns all about Hoda Kotb’s morning routine, and Ben Platt and Cookie perform a sweet duet.
summaries.full: Elmo does some hard-hitting journalism to learn about Hoda Kotb’s morning routine before challenging her to a game of "Hot Potato." Ben Platt treats Cookie to a song about his very favorite thing. Grover offers his expertise on how to pack Elmo’s backpack for school.

summaries.short: Elmo and John Oliver have the slowest race ever, Sofia Carson sings a lullaby, and poet Kwame Alexander flows on the spot.
summaries.full: Elmo finds out what animal John Oliver would be, and the two compete in the world’s slowest and most dramatic race. Sofia Carson joins the slow-mo fun with a lovely lullaby, and Kwame Alexander recites an impromptu poem about - who else - Elmo!
